{
  "doc_id": "25201",
  "text": "A second example of a novel switch is the pair of serotonin-receptor genes HTR1A and HTR5A. Serotonin is a major neuromodulator involved in regulation of mood [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , aggressive behavior [CITATION_4] , and sleep-wake cycle [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Importantly, serotonin is involved in major mood pathologies like depression and aggressive behavior, and selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs) are today the most widely used anti-depressants. There are seven families of serotonin receptors, each containing multiple subunits. We focus here on two specific proteins 5-HT 1A and 5-HT 5A which are both compounds of G αi -coupled inhibitory receptors 5-HT 1 and 5-HT [CITATION_7] .",
